{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01M5ZuU7GngkufmPuRhSjm2h","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have enough information. Let me create a comprehensive summary document of all the files and conventions you need to understand to implement F17:\n\n## Summary: Codebase Conventions for F17 Implementation\n\nBased on my exploration of the codebase, here's everything you need to know to implement F17 correctly:\n\n### 1. Package.json & Test/Build Commands\n\n**File**: `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/package.json`\n\nKey scripts:\n- `npm test` / `pnpm test` → runs `vitest run`\n- `npm run lint` / `pnpm lint` → runs `biome check`\n- `npm run lint:fix` / `pnpm lint:fix` → runs `biome check --fix`\n- `npm run typecheck` / `pnpm typecheck` → runs `tsc --noEmit`\n- `npm run build` / `pnpm build` → runs `next build`\n\nDependencies: @clickhouse/client 1.18.2, Next.js 16.2.3, React 19.2.4, TypeScript 5, vitest 4.1.4\n\n### 2. Vitest Configuration\n\n**File**: `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/vitest.config.ts`\n\nKey settings:\n- Environment: `node`\n- Alias: `@` → `src/`\n- Excludes: playwright tests\n\n### 3. Test File Patterns\n\n**Example files**:\n- `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/app/api/trends/__tests__/route.test.ts`\n- `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/app/api/funnels/__tests__/route.test.ts`\n- `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/app/api/users/__tests__/route.test.ts`\n- `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/scripts/__tests__/migrate.test.ts`\n\n**Test patterns to follow**:\n- Tests are co-located in `__tests__/` subdirectories adjacent to the code being tested\n- For API routes: `src/app/api/{feature}/__tests__/route.test.ts`\n- For libs: `src/lib/__tests__/{feature}.test.ts`\n- Use `vi.hoisted()` for mock setup before imports\n- Use `vi.mock()` for module mocking\n- Structure with `beforeEach`, `afterEach`, and `describe`/`it` blocks\n- Use `expect()` assertions with matchers like `.toBe()`, `.toHaveProperty()`, `.toEqual()`\n- Mock function spy pattern: `mockFn.mockResolvedValue()`, `mockFn.mockRejectedValue()`\n- Create helper functions for request construction in route tests (e.g., `makeRequest()`)\n\n### 4. ClickHouse Client Singleton\n\n**File**: `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/lib/clickhouse.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport { createClient } from \"@clickhouse/client\";\n\nexport const clickhouse = createClient({\n  url: process.env.CLICKHOUSE_URL ?? \"http://localhost:8123\",\n  database: process.env.CLICKHOUSE_DB ?? \"minipanel\",\n  password: process.env.CLICKHOUSE_PASSWORD ?? \"password\",\n});\n```\n\n- Always use the singleton `clickhouse` client for queries\n- Support dependency injection: `client: ClickHouseClientLike = clickhouse` pattern\n- Type alias: `type ClickHouseClientLike = typeof clickhouse`\n\n### 5. Identity Module (EventRow Type & Query Patterns)\n\n**File**: `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/lib/identity.ts`\n\nKey exports:\n```typescript\nexport interface EventRow {\n  event_id: string;\n  event_name: string;\n  timestamp: string;\n  device_id: string | null;\n  user_id: string | null;\n  properties: string;  // JSON stringified\n  ingested_at: string;\n  resolved_id: string;\n}\n\nexport interface QueryEventsOptions {\n  event_name?: string;\n  resolved_id?: string;\n  before?: string;  // ISO timestamp cursor\n  limit?: number;\n}\n\nexport async function queryEventsWithResolvedId(\n  options: QueryEventsOptions = {},\n  client: ClickHouseClientLike = clickhouse,\n): Promise<EventRow[]>\n```\n\n**Key pattern for resolved_id resolution**:\n```sql\nLEFT JOIN (SELECT device_id, user_id FROM identity_mappings FINAL) m\n  ON e.device_id = m.device_id\nSELECT\n  ...\n  coalesce(e.user_id, m.user_id, e.device_id) AS resolved_id\n```\n\n- `resolved_id` = `coalesce(user_id, mapped_user_id, device_id)`\n- Always use `FINAL` keyword with identity_mappings (for consistency)\n- Order by `timestamp DESC, event_id DESC` for pagination\n- Limit to max 200 (or configurable per call)\n\n### 6. API Route Structure\n\n**Examples**:\n- Simple query route: `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/app/api/trends/route.ts`\n- POST with body validation: `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/app/api/funnels/route.ts`\n- GET with stream: `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/app/api/events/list/route.ts`\n\n**API Route conventions**:\n- One file per HTTP method: `export async function GET()`, `export async function POST()`\n- Always return `Response` objects\n- Use `Response.json(data, { status: code })` for JSON responses\n- Use `Response.json({ error: \"message\" }, { status: 400 })` for errors\n- Validate query params/body early, return 400 on validation failure\n- Return 500 on unexpected errors with `{ error: message }`\n- For stream responses: return `new Response(stream, { headers })`\n- Parse URL params: `const { searchParams } = new URL(request.url); searchParams.get(\"key\")`\n- Parse body: try `await request.json()` in try-catch, return 400 on JSON parse error\n\n**Error handling pattern**:\n```typescript\ntry {\n  // main logic\n} catch (err) {\n  const message = err instanceof Error ? err.message : \"Internal server error.\";\n  return Response.json({ error: message }, { status: 500 });\n}\n```\n\n### 7. Lib Module Structure\n\nExample: `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/lib/trends.ts`\n\n**Patterns**:\n- Export types/interfaces first\n- Type alias for client: `type ClickHouseClientLike = typeof clickhouse`\n- Internal helpers (with `function` keyword) at top\n- Main query function with optional client parameter\n- Document with JSDoc comments\n- Use `query_params` for parameterized queries\n- Return parsed JSON from ClickHouse queries\n\n### 8. F17 Requirements (From F17-plan.md)\n\n**Acceptance criteria**:\n- `GET /api/live` returns `text/event-stream` (Server-Sent Events)\n- Polls ClickHouse every 1 second for events with `ingested_at > last_seen`\n- Each event is sent as: `data: {\"event_id\":\"...\",\"event_name\":\"...\",\"resolved_id\":\"...\",\"timestamp\":\"...\",\"properties\":{...}}\\n\\n`\n- Response headers: `Content-Type: text/event-stream`, `Cache-Control: no-cache`, `Connection: keep-alive`\n\n**Files to create**:\n1. `src/lib/live.ts` — Export `queryNewEvents(sinceIngestedAt: string, client?)` function\n2. `src/app/api/live/route.ts` — Export `GET` handler with streaming response\n3. `src/lib/__tests__/live.test.ts` — Unit tests for query function\n4. `src/app/api/live/__tests__/route.test.ts` — Unit tests for route handler\n\n**Implementation details**:\n- `queryNewEvents` should query events joined with identity_mappings FINAL\n- Filter: `e.ingested_at > {since:String}`\n- Order: `e.ingested_at ASC, e.event_id ASC` (oldest first)\n- Limit: 200 (reasonable batch size)\n- Returns: `EventRow[]`\n- Route initializes watermark to current server time\n- Each poll tick: query new events, write as SSE lines, advance watermark\n- Handle client disconnect via `signal.aborted` / `controller.close()`\n\n**Directory structure** (already exists):\n- `src/lib/__tests__/` — 10 existing test files\n- `src/app/api/` — contains 10 route.ts files across different endpoints\n\n---\n\n### Key Conventions Summary\n\n1. **Naming**: Use lowercase, dash-separated for file/folder names; camelCase for functions/vars\n2. **Imports**: Use `@/` alias for imports from `src/`\n3. **Error handling**: Distinguish error types (400 validation, 409 conflict, 500 internal)\n4. **Testing**: Mock modules at the top with `vi.hoisted()`, use named test descriptions\n5. **Query building**: Export a separate `buildQuery()` function for unit testing\n6. **Types**: Define `ClickHouseClientLike` type alias, support optional client injection\n7. **Comments**: Use `─── Section ────` style headers for visual organization\n8. **Validation**: Do param validation in the route, not in the lib function\n\nYou're now ready to implement F17 following these established conventions!"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0753a1fd-dd5e-4de5-9e44-2e4e736c96a0","uuid":"5dd305b0-fe53-4d3b-9a25-ac93334aef88","timestamp":"2026-04-15T15:15:43.274Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase at /Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2 to understand conventions for implementing F17. I need to:\n\n1. Read package.json to understand test/lint/build commands and dependencies\n2. Read vitest config files (vitest.config.ts or similar)\n3. Read 2-3 existing test files to understand patterns (look in src/lib/__tests__/ or similar)\n4. Read src/lib/clickhouse.ts - the ClickHouse client singleton\n5. Read src/lib/identity.ts - for EventRow type and query patterns\n6. Read any existing API route files like src/app/api/events/route.ts or src/app/api/funnels/route.ts\n7. Check what's in features/ directory (specifically F17-plan.md if present)\n8. Check src/app/api/ directory structure\n\nPlease read all these files and report their full contents so I can implement F17 correctly.","agentId":"a9fdbec4a554f8ee3","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have enough information. Let me create a comprehensive summary document of all the files and conventions you need to understand to implement F17:\n\n## Summary: Codebase Conventions for F17 Implementation\n\nBased on my exploration of the codebase, here's everything you need to know to implement F17 correctly:\n\n### 1. Package.json & Test/Build Commands\n\n**File**: `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/package.json`\n\nKey scripts:\n- `npm test` / `pnpm test` → runs `vitest run`\n- `npm run lint` / `pnpm lint` → runs `biome ch